author: Sarah Meehan
title: WOW Air is offering flights to Dublin from BWI for $99
text: WOW Air is offering flights to Dublin from BWI for $99 Jul 6, 2015, 2:59pm EDT Enlarge European discount airline WOW Air will begin offering round-trip flights from BWI to… more WOW Air, the discount European airline, has started offering flights from Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport to Dublin for as low as $99 one way — with a short layover. The twice-weekly flights, which route through Reykjavik, Iceland, began July 6. Iceland-based WOW Air launched service out of BWI in May with flights to Reykjavik and connections to Amsterdam, Berlin, Copenhagen, London and Paris. CEO Skuli Mogensen said during a May visit to BWI that he hopes to grow the airline's international service to the Baltimore airport. Bizspace Spotlight
